1
00:00:01,001 --> 00:00:03,401
ASHAD: The Cybermen
were defeated.

2
00:00:05,041 --> 00:00:08,681
The victors of
a billion battles, broken.

3
00:00:08,801 --> 00:00:12,241
An empire of might and terror,
fallen.

4
00:00:13,841 --> 00:00:15,841
Their weaknesses exploited.

5
00:00:15,961 --> 00:00:18,601
Their armies outfought.

6
00:00:18,721 --> 00:00:20,881
Their conquests surrendered.

7
00:00:22,521 --> 00:00:25,281
Every empire has its time.

8
00:00:26,481 --> 00:00:28,961
And every empire falls.

9
00:00:30,001 --> 00:00:34,041
But that which is dead
can live again...

10
00:00:35,081 --> 00:00:38,721
...in the hands of a believer.

11
00:01:37,321 --> 00:01:39,281
(BABY GURGLES)

12
00:02:01,241 --> 00:02:03,961
MICHAEL: And you say
you just found it in the lane?

13
00:02:04,081 --> 00:02:05,801
I did.

14
00:02:05,921 --> 00:02:07,121
Like that?

15
00:02:07,241 --> 00:02:08,441
Like that.

16
00:02:08,561 --> 00:02:10,561
No note?

17
00:02:13,361 --> 00:02:15,841
We'll look after him.

18
00:02:17,641 --> 00:02:19,881
(STAMMERS)
Until you find the parents.

19
00:02:26,401 --> 00:02:28,641
That's right.

20
00:02:35,161 --> 00:02:38,521
(BABY CRIES)

21
00:02:42,321 --> 00:02:43,681
Well?

22
00:02:45,481 --> 00:02:46,921
It's official.

23
00:02:47,041 --> 00:02:48,441
(MEG GASPS)

24
00:02:48,561 --> 00:02:49,961
He's ours!

25
00:02:53,161 --> 00:02:54,081
Oh!

26
00:02:54,201 --> 00:02:56,121
(BOTH LAUGH)

27
00:02:56,241 --> 00:02:58,041
Oh, our beautiful baby boy.

28
00:02:59,081 --> 00:03:01,601
Aren't you, Brendan?

29
00:03:11,521 --> 00:03:13,161
- Woohoo!
- There you go.

30
00:03:13,281 --> 00:03:14,241
Let's go. Let's go.

31
00:03:14,361 --> 00:03:16,281
- Ready for your first day?
- Yeah.

32
00:03:16,401 --> 00:03:17,801
- Oh, oh, in you go!
- Argh!

33
00:03:17,921 --> 00:03:20,201
The muscles of ya! Good lad.

34
00:03:20,321 --> 00:03:21,801
That's a good lad.

35
00:03:24,321 --> 00:03:26,041
Oh!

36
00:03:26,161 --> 00:03:28,121
Aaah...

37
00:03:36,201 --> 00:03:39,201
If it gets worse,
I'll call the doctor.

38
00:03:39,521 --> 00:03:40,921
(PANTING)

39
00:03:41,041 --> 00:03:42,401
Half a mile out.

40
00:03:42,521 --> 00:03:44,801
The exact coordinates
Shelley gave us...

41
00:03:44,921 --> 00:03:46,441
...are just down there.

42
00:03:46,561 --> 00:03:49,281
GRAHAM: You want us to lug
all this stuff down there?

43
00:03:49,401 --> 00:03:50,321
What's wrong, Graham?

44
00:03:50,441 --> 00:03:52,321
Can't take
the commando lifestyle?

45
00:03:52,441 --> 00:03:53,881
RYAN: Hey!
No commando jokes, please.

46
00:03:54,001 --> 00:03:56,081
I don't need that image
in me head.

47
00:03:56,201 --> 00:03:57,641
Any ideas
what we're walking into?

48
00:03:57,761 --> 00:04:00,281
This planet, this time period -

49
00:04:00,401 --> 00:04:02,241
we're in the very far future,

50
00:04:02,361 --> 00:04:04,201
immediate aftermath
of the Cyber Wars.

51
00:04:04,321 --> 00:04:06,401
Cybermen have hunted down
and wiped out

52
00:04:06,521 --> 00:04:08,321
the majority of the human race.

53
00:04:13,721 --> 00:04:15,681
Sorry. It was never a good time
to break that news to you.

54
00:04:15,801 --> 00:04:16,881
If it's any consolation,

55
00:04:17,001 --> 00:04:18,241
it almost wiped out
the Cybermen too.

56
00:04:18,361 --> 00:04:20,361
Yeah, but almost
isn't good enough, is it?

57
00:04:20,481 --> 00:04:21,801
- (SONIC BUZZES)
- No.

58
00:04:23,241 --> 00:04:25,681
I'm getting a handful
of human life signs down there.

59
00:04:25,801 --> 00:04:28,161
When you say a handful,
how much are we talking?

60
00:04:28,281 --> 00:04:29,961
Seven.

61
00:04:31,121 --> 00:04:32,961
- Seven humans left?
- If I had to guess,

62
00:04:33,081 --> 00:04:35,161
I'd say that's the last
remaining human settlement

63
00:04:35,281 --> 00:04:37,321
this side of the universe
right now.

64
00:04:43,601 --> 00:04:44,841
How are the repairs?

65
00:04:44,961 --> 00:04:46,041
Piece of cake.

66
00:04:46,161 --> 00:04:47,641
Gravraft's completely fixed,

67
00:04:47,761 --> 00:04:49,441
completely fine,
we're good to go.

68
00:04:49,561 --> 00:04:51,361
- Really?
- No.

69
00:04:51,481 --> 00:04:53,361
But you always look at me
with those puppy dog eyes

70
00:04:53,481 --> 00:04:55,001
and say, "Please tell me
it's good news."

71
00:04:55,121 --> 00:04:56,241
How long will it take?

72
00:04:56,361 --> 00:04:57,921
A day, maybe more.

73
00:04:58,041 --> 00:05:00,001
I promise
I'm doing everything I can.

74
00:05:00,121 --> 00:05:02,561
I know you are, but those
last signal bursts indicated

75
00:05:02,681 --> 00:05:05,001
- that we don't...
- (REVERBERATING BOOM)

76
00:05:05,121 --> 00:05:06,441
It's too soon.

77
00:05:15,081 --> 00:05:16,961
You said
there weren't any more.

78
00:05:17,081 --> 00:05:18,721
You said they wouldn't find us!

79
00:05:18,841 --> 00:05:20,401
- They always find us.
- I said I hoped

80
00:05:20,521 --> 00:05:21,961
there weren't any left.

81
00:05:22,081 --> 00:05:24,481
You said it was too good
to be true.

82
00:05:24,601 --> 00:05:26,601
Yeah, well, sometimes
I just want to be wrong.

83
00:05:26,721 --> 00:05:28,841
Question -
would you like some help?

84
00:05:28,961 --> 00:05:30,041
(BLASTER POWERS UP)

85
00:05:30,161 --> 00:05:31,921
You don't need to use that
against us.

86
00:05:32,041 --> 00:05:33,441
Who are you?

87
00:05:33,561 --> 00:05:34,961
Where did you come from?

88
00:05:35,081 --> 00:05:37,201
Doctor, Graham, Ryan and Yaz.

89
00:05:37,321 --> 00:05:38,681
Don't worry about
where we're from -

90
00:05:38,801 --> 00:05:40,201
concentrate on how we can help.

91
00:05:41,761 --> 00:05:43,081
(BLASTER POWERS DOWN)

92
00:05:43,201 --> 00:05:44,961
All right. Set this all up
like I showed you.

93
00:05:47,441 --> 00:05:49,361
(SONIC BUZZES)

94
00:05:49,481 --> 00:05:51,481
Two cyber shuttles,
just landing.

95
00:05:51,601 --> 00:05:52,641
- Who's in charge?
- I-I guess

96
00:05:52,761 --> 00:05:54,401
I am, as much as anyone is.

97
00:05:54,521 --> 00:05:55,681
Fought Cybermen before?

98
00:05:55,801 --> 00:05:57,841
No. We've run from them.

99
00:05:57,961 --> 00:05:59,761
- Escape craft?
- Damaged in planet fall.

100
00:05:59,881 --> 00:06:02,081
I've been trying to fix it,
but we've got no spare parts.

101
00:06:02,201 --> 00:06:05,121
- I've botch-built a couple...
- Don't need your life story.

102
00:06:05,241 --> 00:06:06,681
Get everybody
into the buildings

103
00:06:06,801 --> 00:06:07,881
and tell them, do not run.

104
00:06:08,001 --> 00:06:10,481
Please, do as I say.

105
00:06:10,601 --> 00:06:12,281
You can trust us.

106
00:06:12,401 --> 00:06:14,761
GRAHAM: Bish bash bosh.

107
00:06:14,881 --> 00:06:16,561
- What's that?
- This, cockle,

108
00:06:16,681 --> 00:06:18,161
- is a neural inhibitor system.
- A what?

109
00:06:18,281 --> 00:06:20,081
Yeah, I didn't have a clue
either.

110
00:06:20,201 --> 00:06:21,361
As far as I understand it,

111
00:06:21,481 --> 00:06:23,121
your basic Cyberman
is part-human,

112
00:06:23,241 --> 00:06:26,001
part-machine.
Now, they have suppressed

113
00:06:26,121 --> 00:06:27,921
all emotion
and sensations of pain,

114
00:06:28,041 --> 00:06:29,761
which means
if we can un-suppress those

115
00:06:29,881 --> 00:06:31,961
and they realise what's
happening to their bodies,

116
00:06:32,081 --> 00:06:33,241
it sends them a bit mad,

117
00:06:33,361 --> 00:06:34,681
which is one way
of stopping them.

118
00:06:34,801 --> 00:06:37,281
And that is what this gizmo
is supposed to be doing.

119
00:06:37,401 --> 00:06:38,801
- And will it definitely work?
- Well, I hope so, son,

120
00:06:38,921 --> 00:06:40,401
cos we've come a long way.
Now, do us a favour,

121
00:06:40,521 --> 00:06:42,241
get yourself safe.
There's a good lad.

122
00:06:44,321 --> 00:06:46,481
- What is that thing?
- Particle projector.

123
00:06:46,601 --> 00:06:47,761
The Doctor's customised it

124
00:06:47,881 --> 00:06:49,761
to project particles of gold
into the air.

125
00:06:49,881 --> 00:06:52,161
Cybermen are allergic to gold,
right?

126
00:06:52,281 --> 00:06:53,601
I did hear that once.

127
00:06:54,641 --> 00:06:57,001
I'm going to go and get
the gravraft going.

128
00:06:57,121 --> 00:06:59,361
- Force field?
- Yeah.

129
00:06:59,481 --> 00:07:01,681
Hmm. Yeah, pretty rudimentary.

130
00:07:01,801 --> 00:07:03,401
Yeah, well,
you got a better one?

131
00:07:03,521 --> 00:07:04,721
We ain't got nothin'.

132
00:07:04,841 --> 00:07:06,001
Oi, Fuskle! Here.

133
00:07:06,121 --> 00:07:07,721
He's my little brother.

134
00:07:07,841 --> 00:07:09,561
He don't say much,
not any more.

135
00:07:09,681 --> 00:07:11,281
It's a force field, mate.

136
00:07:11,401 --> 00:07:12,321
And people.

137
00:07:12,441 --> 00:07:14,121
It's got to be good news.
Will you tell him what it does?

138
00:07:14,241 --> 00:07:16,481
It's for any Cyberman
that comes near.

139
00:07:16,601 --> 00:07:19,481
See?
We're going to be all right.

140
00:07:19,601 --> 00:07:23,361
Yedlarmi. And Fuskle.
Well, give him your hand, then.

141
00:07:23,481 --> 00:07:25,961
If you're not going to speak,
at least give him your hand.

142
00:07:27,561 --> 00:07:29,601
- (SONIC BUZZES)
- What are you doing?

143
00:07:29,721 --> 00:07:31,361
Trying to see
where they're coming from.

144
00:07:31,481 --> 00:07:33,441
But they're sending
a jamming signal,

145
00:07:33,561 --> 00:07:35,841
trying to confuse us as to
what they are and how many.

146
00:07:37,241 --> 00:07:38,601
What weapons have you got,
Feekat?

147
00:07:38,721 --> 00:07:40,361
Two guns - one's broken.

148
00:07:40,481 --> 00:07:41,801
So basically nothing?

149
00:07:41,921 --> 00:07:43,521
We're not soldiers.

150
00:07:43,641 --> 00:07:45,041
I was a teacher.

151
00:07:45,161 --> 00:07:46,681
Ravio was a nurse.

152
00:07:46,801 --> 00:07:49,561
We've got a childminder,
a driver, a builder.

153
00:07:49,681 --> 00:07:52,401
We're just ordinary humans,

154
00:07:52,521 --> 00:07:54,241
refugees,

155
00:07:54,361 --> 00:07:56,361
and we've all
lost everything...

156
00:07:56,481 --> 00:07:57,721
...and everyone.

157
00:07:57,841 --> 00:07:59,961
All to the Cybermen.

158
00:08:01,241 --> 00:08:02,641
And nobody cares.

159
00:08:02,761 --> 00:08:04,001
I care.

160
00:08:04,121 --> 00:08:07,161
Me and my friends, we care.

161
00:08:08,921 --> 00:08:11,281
Please,
get inside the building.

162
00:08:11,401 --> 00:08:12,881
We'll fight whatever's coming.

163
00:08:13,001 --> 00:08:13,961
(REVERBERATING BOOM)

164
00:08:15,361 --> 00:08:17,641
Activation time, fam!

165
00:08:17,761 --> 00:08:19,241
Get close. I don't know

166
00:08:19,361 --> 00:08:21,121
how many they are
or which direction

167
00:08:21,241 --> 00:08:22,521
they're coming from.

168
00:08:22,641 --> 00:08:24,361
Quick!

169
00:08:25,441 --> 00:08:27,441
(PROJECTOR POWERS UP)

170
00:08:27,561 --> 00:08:29,721
(ELECTRIC BUZZING)

171
00:08:32,361 --> 00:08:34,921
(WHOOSHING)

172
00:08:35,041 --> 00:08:37,481
Hey. Do you hear that sound?

173
00:08:39,921 --> 00:08:42,521
Stay. Seriously, mate.

174
00:08:42,641 --> 00:08:45,281
I know you're scared.
We're all scared.

175
00:08:50,481 --> 00:08:52,041
Cyberdrones.

176
00:09:02,801 --> 00:09:05,281
Fam, get down!

177
00:09:06,241 --> 00:09:08,481
They're targeting the defences!

178
00:09:11,801 --> 00:09:13,321
(GRAHAM YELLS)

179
00:09:29,721 --> 00:09:31,201
Fuskle!

180
00:09:35,761 --> 00:09:37,361
DOCTOR: No!

181
00:09:37,481 --> 00:09:39,401
Get down!

182
00:09:39,521 --> 00:09:41,481
I said don't run!

183
00:09:41,601 --> 00:09:43,081
Come on!

184
00:09:44,601 --> 00:09:45,881
(YELLS)

185
00:09:46,001 --> 00:09:47,681
Fuskle, don't run!

186
00:09:47,801 --> 00:09:49,281
- No!
- Get back here!

187
00:09:49,401 --> 00:09:52,401
- Fuskle!
- GRAHAM: We can't outrun them!

188
00:09:52,521 --> 00:09:53,961
Fuskle!

189
00:09:57,201 --> 00:09:58,201
Argh!

190
00:09:59,561 --> 00:10:01,721
FEEKAT: Stay in here.

191
00:10:04,081 --> 00:10:06,841
- (DRONES SHRIEK)
- (WHOOSHING)

192
00:10:09,561 --> 00:10:10,881
(UNSTEADY BREATHING)

193
00:10:14,041 --> 00:10:15,561
(FIRE CRACKLING)

194
00:10:15,681 --> 00:10:18,681
Please. Run. Get to your ship.

195
00:10:18,801 --> 00:10:21,481
I am sick of running.

196
00:10:21,601 --> 00:10:22,841
- I want to fight 'em.
- It won't be

197
00:10:22,961 --> 00:10:24,801
a fight, it'll be a massacre.

198
00:10:24,921 --> 00:10:27,601
The drones
are just the advance guard.

199
00:10:27,721 --> 00:10:29,481
I'll buy you some time.

200
00:10:29,601 --> 00:10:31,321
Go. Now!

201
00:10:33,801 --> 00:10:35,401
Come on.

202
00:10:35,521 --> 00:10:36,841
Let's go. You and Ravio

203
00:10:36,961 --> 00:10:38,881
get the gravraft started.
Ethan and I

204
00:10:39,001 --> 00:10:40,441
will grab the supplies.

205
00:10:49,521 --> 00:10:51,401
The systems didn't stop 'em,
Doc.

206
00:10:51,521 --> 00:10:53,361
I know.

207
00:10:53,481 --> 00:10:55,361
They destroyed everything
we brought with us.

208
00:10:55,481 --> 00:10:56,481
- I know.
- We haven't got

209
00:10:56,601 --> 00:10:57,761
anything else
to defend ourselves

210
00:10:57,881 --> 00:10:59,561
- or them.
- I know!

211
00:11:00,641 --> 00:11:02,721
(METALLIC RUMBLING)

212
00:11:02,841 --> 00:11:05,801
Listen to me. Do not argue.
Go with the humans.

213
00:11:05,921 --> 00:11:07,521
Help them.
Get them out of here.

214
00:11:07,641 --> 00:11:09,361
You won't make it
back to the TARDIS alive.

215
00:11:09,481 --> 00:11:10,921
Make sure you're with them.

216
00:11:11,041 --> 00:11:12,681
- What about you?
- I'll hold them off.

217
00:11:12,801 --> 00:11:13,561
How are you going to do that?

218
00:11:13,681 --> 00:11:15,081
- This isn't a discussion.
- We're not

219
00:11:15,201 --> 00:11:17,401
- just going to leave you.
- Yes, you are!

220
00:11:18,361 --> 00:11:19,881
You have to, all of you.

221
00:11:20,001 --> 00:11:22,361
No questions. Get out.

222
00:11:24,721 --> 00:11:26,481
I've been so reckless with you.

223
00:11:26,601 --> 00:11:28,521
- What are you talking about?
- You're human!

224
00:11:28,641 --> 00:11:31,161
If they capture you,
they'll convert you.

225
00:11:32,921 --> 00:11:34,561
(CLUNKING FOOTSTEPS)

226
00:11:34,681 --> 00:11:36,161
I'll find you.

227
00:11:37,601 --> 00:11:39,361
Get safe - now!

228
00:11:39,481 --> 00:11:41,681
(CLUNKING FOOTSTEPS)

229
00:11:54,681 --> 00:11:56,841
Yeah, me again!

230
00:11:56,961 --> 00:11:58,561
(WHIR)

231
00:11:58,681 --> 00:12:00,521
Here to stop you for good
this time.

232
00:12:00,641 --> 00:12:02,721
It's just you and me.

233
00:12:02,841 --> 00:12:05,761
(STOMPING FOOTSTEPS APPROACH)

234
00:12:05,881 --> 00:12:09,001
CYBERGUARD:
Strategic defences destroyed.

235
00:12:09,121 --> 00:12:12,481
- Life signs identified.
- Or not.

236
00:12:12,601 --> 00:12:14,401
All humans will be deleted.

237
00:12:14,521 --> 00:12:16,121
Rethink.

238
00:12:17,521 --> 00:12:19,041
Keep the others safe.

239
00:12:21,121 --> 00:12:23,081
Act as bait. See ya!

240
00:12:24,121 --> 00:12:25,321
GRAHAM: Go, go, go!

241
00:12:27,881 --> 00:12:29,321
(YAZ YELPS)

242
00:12:29,441 --> 00:12:33,161
Three targets acquired. Delete.

243
00:12:33,281 --> 00:12:34,681
RYAN: Keep going!

244
00:12:36,001 --> 00:12:37,201
(YAZ SCREAMS)

245
00:12:39,881 --> 00:12:41,761
Surrender, humans.

246
00:12:41,881 --> 00:12:43,761
YAZ: Get out of here!

247
00:12:43,881 --> 00:12:45,561
There are Cybermen behind us!

248
00:12:45,681 --> 00:12:48,681
We're not ready.
I haven't got Feekat and Ethan.

249
00:12:48,801 --> 00:12:50,201
Listen to Yaz - get inside.

250
00:12:52,601 --> 00:12:53,761
Graham, where's Ryan?

251
00:12:55,281 --> 00:12:57,041
Get inside the gravraft!

252
00:12:57,161 --> 00:12:58,961
No, no, we've got to find
our friends!

253
00:13:01,201 --> 00:13:03,521
Get inside
if you want to stay alive!

254
00:13:03,641 --> 00:13:06,281
- Ryan!
- Get inside!

255
00:13:06,401 --> 00:13:08,121
Go! Expedite takeoff - now!

256
00:13:08,241 --> 00:13:10,641
What are you doing?
We can't take this lot.

257
00:13:10,761 --> 00:13:13,321
(SHOTS RICOCHETING)

258
00:13:13,441 --> 00:13:17,041
Fuskle's dead because
their stuff didn't work.

259
00:13:18,721 --> 00:13:20,641
Yedlarmi, I'm sorry.

260
00:13:20,761 --> 00:13:22,921
Their weapons
are going to destroy

261
00:13:23,041 --> 00:13:25,361
the outer shell -
we need to go now!

262
00:13:26,401 --> 00:13:28,521
- Not without the others.
- The others are dead.

263
00:13:28,641 --> 00:13:29,601
We all know it's true.

264
00:13:29,721 --> 00:13:30,841
If they haven't got here
by now,

265
00:13:30,961 --> 00:13:32,001
that thing must've got 'em.

266
00:13:32,121 --> 00:13:33,401
Look, we've only come in here
for shelter,

267
00:13:33,521 --> 00:13:34,641
and our friends
are still out there.

268
00:13:34,761 --> 00:13:35,401
Sit down!

269
00:13:35,521 --> 00:13:36,681
Our friends are still outside!

270
00:13:36,801 --> 00:13:38,041
No! You need to let us out!

271
00:13:38,161 --> 00:13:39,401
It's too late.

272
00:13:39,521 --> 00:13:41,161
(BANG!)

273
00:13:43,761 --> 00:13:45,721
(GRUNTS)

274
00:14:11,881 --> 00:14:13,481
Shh!
What are you still doing here?

275
00:14:13,601 --> 00:14:16,041
I told you to get out.
We got separated.

276
00:14:16,161 --> 00:14:18,001
- (BEEPING)
- Hey, what's that?

277
00:14:18,121 --> 00:14:20,401
Final fallback option
to get us out alive.

278
00:14:20,521 --> 00:14:21,481
(SONIC BUZZES)

279
00:14:21,601 --> 00:14:24,121
(HEAVY FOOTSTEPS APPROACH)

280
00:14:41,681 --> 00:14:43,361
(WHIRRING)

281
00:14:44,521 --> 00:14:46,201
What's it doing?

282
00:14:46,321 --> 00:14:47,721
Shh!

283
00:14:49,001 --> 00:14:51,721
I know you're here.

284
00:14:55,521 --> 00:14:57,121
Surrender!

285
00:14:58,201 --> 00:14:59,201
WHISPERS: Hey.

286
00:15:01,001 --> 00:15:02,241
Stay here.

287
00:15:03,441 --> 00:15:05,481
- Ethan, no!
- ETHAN: I'm here.

288
00:15:07,801 --> 00:15:09,361
It's just me.

289
00:15:09,481 --> 00:15:11,161
No-one else.

290
00:15:11,281 --> 00:15:12,681
I surrender.

291
00:15:13,721 --> 00:15:15,121
You can take me.

292
00:15:19,001 --> 00:15:21,921
You show courage.

293
00:15:23,481 --> 00:15:25,881
But you're a liar!

294
00:15:35,761 --> 00:15:37,681
So few of you now.

295
00:15:39,401 --> 00:15:40,921
Should I let you live?

296
00:15:42,801 --> 00:15:45,161
You could tell the tale -

297
00:15:45,281 --> 00:15:47,001
speak of their deaths,

298
00:15:47,121 --> 00:15:48,641
of my power,

299
00:15:48,761 --> 00:15:52,161
to every other species.

300
00:15:56,801 --> 00:15:58,921
Spread my message.

301
00:15:59,041 --> 00:16:02,081
Tell them, "Be afraid.

302
00:16:02,201 --> 00:16:05,841
"All humanity have been erased.

303
00:16:05,961 --> 00:16:08,201
"All Llife will fall.

304
00:16:08,321 --> 00:16:12,361
"And the Cybermen
will rise again."

305
00:16:12,481 --> 00:16:13,841
Not if I have
anything to do with it.

306
00:16:14,881 --> 00:16:16,201
Run!

307
00:16:16,321 --> 00:16:17,321
Go!

308
00:16:19,681 --> 00:16:22,441
Doctor, we've got to find Yaz
and Graham.

309
00:16:22,561 --> 00:16:24,121
I saw them get on the gravraft.
They're gone.

310
00:16:24,241 --> 00:16:25,361
What?

311
00:16:25,481 --> 00:16:27,241
Concentrate, Ryan,
we have to get out of here.

312
00:16:27,361 --> 00:16:29,201
We can't make it to the TARDIS,
no escape ship,

313
00:16:29,321 --> 00:16:30,401
a relentless Cyberman

314
00:16:30,521 --> 00:16:31,721
and very limited options.

315
00:16:31,841 --> 00:16:34,201
Well, one option.
How fast are you feeling?

316
00:16:34,321 --> 00:16:35,641
Come on.

317
00:16:38,921 --> 00:16:40,321
RYAN: Are we going
to steal their ship?

318
00:16:40,441 --> 00:16:41,441
DOCTOR: Yes, we are!

319
00:16:44,401 --> 00:16:46,841
Hot-wiring a Cyberfighter.

320
00:16:46,961 --> 00:16:48,321
(GRUNTS)

321
00:16:48,441 --> 00:16:49,641
Oh, it's warp.

322
00:16:49,761 --> 00:16:51,521
Of course! Which makes it
trickier, unless you're me,

323
00:16:51,641 --> 00:16:53,281
which I am, which is good,

324
00:16:53,401 --> 00:16:55,601
cos I used to hot-wire
warp drives for fun

325
00:16:55,721 --> 00:16:56,921
on a weekend as a teenager.

326
00:16:57,041 --> 00:16:58,201
Not that we had weekends.

327
00:16:58,321 --> 00:16:59,241
Or teenagers.

328
00:16:59,361 --> 00:17:01,041
Basically, I used to do this
a lot and people got mad.

329
00:17:01,161 --> 00:17:02,721
But now it's going
to save all our lives,

330
00:17:02,841 --> 00:17:04,321
so who was right all along
and is now the real winner?

331
00:17:04,441 --> 00:17:07,281
There's a faster way.
Here. Let me.

332
00:17:08,441 --> 00:17:10,921
Hey, do you need help
with that, kid?

333
00:17:11,041 --> 00:17:12,921
Who are you calling kid?

334
00:17:13,041 --> 00:17:15,441
(SHIP POWERS UP)

335
00:17:16,681 --> 00:17:18,081
This is going to
make him cross.

336
00:17:18,201 --> 00:17:19,281
Here we go.

337
00:17:21,361 --> 00:17:23,921
Hold on. Hate these controls.

338
00:17:24,041 --> 00:17:25,361
(GRUNTS)

339
00:17:28,761 --> 00:17:31,961
CYBERGUARD: Cyber shuttle theft
in progress, leader.

340
00:17:32,081 --> 00:17:35,281
Human life signs aboard.

341
00:17:37,721 --> 00:17:39,321
(GROWLS)

342
00:17:44,321 --> 00:17:46,801
- Mam!
- Sorry.

343
00:17:46,921 --> 00:17:48,401
Very smart.

344
00:17:51,201 --> 00:17:52,481
Ready, then, son?

345
00:18:12,801 --> 00:18:14,641
It's a good form.

346
00:18:16,721 --> 00:18:18,161
You've done a good job on this.

347
00:18:19,401 --> 00:18:20,961
Very neat handwriting.

348
00:18:25,921 --> 00:18:27,961
And why do you want to be
a guard, Brendan?

349
00:18:30,801 --> 00:18:32,201
He wants to serve.

350
00:18:32,321 --> 00:18:35,681
Best leave the lad to
speak for himself, eh, Pat?

351
00:18:35,801 --> 00:18:37,801
Right.

352
00:18:42,761 --> 00:18:43,961
I wanna make a difference.

353
00:18:50,601 --> 00:18:53,761
I was with him
the day he found you.

354
00:18:55,721 --> 00:18:56,841
Look at you now.

355
00:19:05,241 --> 00:19:06,641
GRAHAM: Yaz, where are we?

356
00:19:07,801 --> 00:19:09,201
What are we doing here?

357
00:19:09,321 --> 00:19:10,681
I think we're stuck
with this lot.

358
00:19:10,801 --> 00:19:12,721
How are we going to get back
to the Doc and Ryan?

359
00:19:15,081 --> 00:19:17,361
Don't worry, we'll find them.

360
00:19:17,481 --> 00:19:19,401
Well, and how
are we going to do that?

361
00:19:19,521 --> 00:19:21,161
Me and you, together?

362
00:19:21,281 --> 00:19:22,561
No-one else stands a chance.

363
00:19:22,681 --> 00:19:23,761
(BEEPING)

364
00:19:23,881 --> 00:19:26,001
Whoa, whoa, whoa,
you're pushing it too hard.

365
00:19:26,121 --> 00:19:27,201
Don't tell me
how to work this thing.

366
00:19:27,321 --> 00:19:28,681
Who's the one who salvaged
this thing in the first place?

367
00:19:28,801 --> 00:19:29,841
Yeah, and who patched it up?

368
00:19:29,961 --> 00:19:32,561
You'll wreck it if you push it
past half power, seriously.

369
00:19:32,681 --> 00:19:34,081
Look how low
the life support has got.

370
00:19:34,201 --> 00:19:36,401
We won't get there
at anything less than 90%.

371
00:19:36,521 --> 00:19:38,641
We won't make it at all
if you push it past 90!

372
00:19:39,721 --> 00:19:41,001
Make it where?

373
00:19:41,121 --> 00:19:43,001
To Ko Sharmus.

374
00:19:44,081 --> 00:19:45,401
And the Boundary.

375
00:19:46,561 --> 00:19:48,521
It's where we've been trying
to get to.

376
00:19:48,641 --> 00:19:50,281
Our only point of safety.

377
00:19:50,401 --> 00:19:51,681
Yeah,
that's what we've been told.

378
00:19:51,801 --> 00:19:53,161
You've got to believe,
Yedlarmi.

379
00:19:53,281 --> 00:19:54,281
Do we?

380
00:19:54,401 --> 00:19:56,401
- How's that working for us?
- It's the best we've got.

381
00:19:57,481 --> 00:19:59,041
And what Boundary
are you talking about?

382
00:19:59,161 --> 00:20:01,841
Supposedly
a way out of this galaxy.

383
00:20:01,961 --> 00:20:03,721
A gateway,
a direct route out of here,

384
00:20:03,841 --> 00:20:06,001
into another random part
of the universe.

385
00:20:06,121 --> 00:20:09,241
We get through there,
the Cybermen can't follow.

386
00:20:09,361 --> 00:20:12,441
The Boundary patterns
are never the same twice.

387
00:20:12,561 --> 00:20:15,801
It's our best hope
of safe harbour.

388
00:20:15,921 --> 00:20:17,641
Energy parcelling's cratering.

389
00:20:17,761 --> 00:20:19,761
Didn't I say
you were pushing it too hard?!

390
00:20:19,881 --> 00:20:21,681
- It's fine.
- What did I tell you?

391
00:20:21,801 --> 00:20:23,201
- It's fine!
- 14 breaches

392
00:20:23,321 --> 00:20:25,521
- in the shell lining.
- Oxygen pressure's dropping.

393
00:20:25,641 --> 00:20:27,401
Energy cells compromised.

394
00:20:27,521 --> 00:20:29,241
Contents getting critical.

395
00:20:29,361 --> 00:20:31,361
- Ah!
- OK, it's not fine.

396
00:20:31,481 --> 00:20:33,081
The whole system's
melting down!

397
00:20:33,201 --> 00:20:34,921
It can't, not here.

398
00:20:35,041 --> 00:20:37,161
It's going to blow. Get down!

399
00:20:37,281 --> 00:20:38,761
(ALARM BLARES)

400
00:20:42,921 --> 00:20:44,521
- (BOOM)
- (RYAN GROANS)

401
00:20:44,641 --> 00:20:46,801
This is rough.

402
00:20:46,921 --> 00:20:47,921
It's making me feel sick.

403
00:20:48,041 --> 00:20:50,401
Cyber warp tech -
not designed for humans. Ooh!

404
00:20:50,521 --> 00:20:51,441
Have a humbug.

405
00:20:51,561 --> 00:20:54,241
It'll help. Added ginger.

406
00:20:54,361 --> 00:20:57,201
I've programmed in
the destination of Ko Sharmus.

407
00:20:57,321 --> 00:20:59,281
It's where the others
will be heading.

408
00:20:59,401 --> 00:21:01,841
Now, if this is warp drive,
we'll get there before them.

409
00:21:01,961 --> 00:21:04,361
I've been scanning,
but I can't see them.

410
00:21:04,481 --> 00:21:05,961
Maybe we're already ahead.

411
00:21:07,721 --> 00:21:09,561
What?

412
00:21:09,681 --> 00:21:10,881
You're good at this.

413
00:21:11,001 --> 00:21:12,921
First thing my dad taught me.

414
00:21:13,041 --> 00:21:15,441
How to hijack Cyberships,

415
00:21:15,561 --> 00:21:17,521
how to take 'em apart,

416
00:21:17,641 --> 00:21:19,801
how to burn 'em to the ground.

417
00:21:19,921 --> 00:21:21,321
I was four.

418
00:21:21,441 --> 00:21:23,001
Born in wartime.

419
00:21:23,121 --> 00:21:24,601
So this is all
you've ever known?

420
00:21:24,721 --> 00:21:26,921
The war made us pariahs,

421
00:21:27,041 --> 00:21:28,721
cos of what was
always coming for us.

422
00:21:30,041 --> 00:21:32,121
The last Cybermen,

423
00:21:32,241 --> 00:21:34,401
intent on destroying
the last humans.

424
00:21:34,521 --> 00:21:36,721
(THE DOCTOR YELPS)

425
00:21:38,681 --> 00:21:42,361
Ah! Here he is, the bad penny.

426
00:21:42,481 --> 00:21:43,761
We were just talking
about you.

427
00:21:43,881 --> 00:21:45,921
We know where you are.

428
00:21:46,041 --> 00:21:47,521
We will find you.

429
00:21:47,641 --> 00:21:48,841
Yeah, yeah. Have you not asked

430
00:21:48,961 --> 00:21:51,721
that great slab of Cyber Al
you absorbed about me?

431
00:21:51,841 --> 00:21:53,081
I'm the Doctor.

432
00:21:53,201 --> 00:21:55,241
Consult the Cyberium, mate.

433
00:21:55,361 --> 00:21:57,241
I've stopped you lot
so many times before,

434
00:21:57,361 --> 00:22:01,361
and I'll do it again,
time after time after time.

435
00:22:01,481 --> 00:22:03,081
No.

436
00:22:03,201 --> 00:22:05,481
The Cyberium does know you.

437
00:22:05,601 --> 00:22:09,121
Both you and humanity
will be destroyed,

438
00:22:09,241 --> 00:22:11,721
and I shall bring
the Cyber race

439
00:22:11,841 --> 00:22:15,001
to its greatest ever glory.

440
00:22:16,041 --> 00:22:18,041
Quite a grudge
you've got against humanity,

441
00:22:18,161 --> 00:22:20,281
especially considering
you used to be one.

442
00:22:20,401 --> 00:22:24,001
When the glorious
Cyber Empire arrived,

443
00:22:24,121 --> 00:22:27,281
I was a willing recruit.

444
00:22:27,401 --> 00:22:29,241
But as I took
my rightful place,

445
00:22:29,361 --> 00:22:31,841
as I began
my blessed ascension...

446
00:22:33,361 --> 00:22:35,561
...] was denied.

447
00:22:37,281 --> 00:22:39,241
At first...

448
00:22:41,441 --> 00:22:46,481
...I cursed myself,
hid in the shadows, ashamed.

449
00:22:48,041 --> 00:22:52,241
But now I understand
I was not discarded.

450
00:22:52,361 --> 00:22:54,921
I was chosen...

451
00:22:55,041 --> 00:23:01,041
...to revive the glory
of the Cyber race.

452
00:23:01,161 --> 00:23:03,801
There's no glory
in being a Cyberman.

453
00:23:03,921 --> 00:23:06,281
And there's definitely no glory
in you.

454
00:23:06,401 --> 00:23:08,801
I mean, talk about
an identity crisis.

455
00:23:08,921 --> 00:23:10,521
You despise who you are.

456
00:23:10,641 --> 00:23:13,881
That anger and hatred
that's driving you?

457
00:23:14,001 --> 00:23:16,441
Those are human emotions.

458
00:23:16,561 --> 00:23:20,641
The real Cybermen,
they don't do emotions.

459
00:23:20,761 --> 00:23:25,161
So you loathe your own being
because of what's driving you.

460
00:23:25,281 --> 00:23:28,361
Now that's what I call
an inner conflict.

461
00:23:28,481 --> 00:23:29,801
Yes.

462
00:23:31,921 --> 00:23:33,961
You are correct.

463
00:23:34,081 --> 00:23:36,801
Oh. Am I? I didn't expect you
to take it that well.

464
00:23:38,121 --> 00:23:40,481
I'll have to bill you
for therapy at this rate.

465
00:23:40,601 --> 00:23:43,721
The Cyberium
has given me understanding.

466
00:23:43,841 --> 00:23:47,481
It has distilled my purpose.

467
00:23:47,601 --> 00:23:49,361
I am the perfect vessel.

468
00:23:49,481 --> 00:23:50,401
Everything is in me

469
00:23:50,521 --> 00:23:52,601
for the ascension
of the Cybermen...

470
00:23:53,921 --> 00:23:55,721
...and beyond.

471
00:23:55,841 --> 00:23:57,801
What do you mean beyond?

472
00:23:57,921 --> 00:23:59,361
What's beyond that?

473
00:23:59,481 --> 00:24:01,801
All your deaths.

474
00:24:06,321 --> 00:24:07,921
The death of everything...

475
00:24:09,201 --> 00:24:10,921
...is within me.

476
00:24:16,241 --> 00:24:17,641
BRENDAN: Stop there, thief!

477
00:24:22,721 --> 00:24:25,121
Eh, come on, then.

478
00:24:25,241 --> 00:24:26,521
Give me the bag.

479
00:24:26,641 --> 00:24:28,321
Everybody gets
their stuff back.

480
00:24:28,441 --> 00:24:29,921
(GUN COCKS)

481
00:24:34,481 --> 00:24:36,561
You don't need to do that.

482
00:24:37,961 --> 00:24:39,041
Move round now.

483
00:24:39,161 --> 00:24:40,561
All right, all right.

484
00:24:45,721 --> 00:24:47,841
Look, I know
you don't want to use that.

485
00:24:49,201 --> 00:24:51,201
(GUNSHOT)

486
00:24:59,441 --> 00:25:00,921
(THUD)

487
00:25:04,761 --> 00:25:05,921
Brendan!

488
00:25:13,201 --> 00:25:14,601
Brendan...

489
00:25:14,721 --> 00:25:16,601
(GASPS FOR AIR)

490
00:25:17,961 --> 00:25:20,281
(BREATHES ERRATICALLY)

491
00:25:20,401 --> 00:25:21,401
I-I'm fine.

492
00:25:22,761 --> 00:25:24,641
I'm fine!

493
00:25:24,761 --> 00:25:26,361
Which way did he go?

494
00:25:26,481 --> 00:25:27,681
Come on.

495
00:25:42,921 --> 00:25:44,801
I was lucky.

496
00:25:52,601 --> 00:25:54,241
MEG: It's a lovely picture.

497
00:25:56,441 --> 00:25:57,921
You look very dashing.

498
00:25:58,041 --> 00:26:00,361
Ma, put it away.

499
00:26:14,001 --> 00:26:15,561
(GROANING)

500
00:26:15,681 --> 00:26:16,801
(GRAHAM EXHALES)

501
00:26:19,481 --> 00:26:20,681
We're still alive!

502
00:26:20,801 --> 00:26:22,321
- Give it time.
- I wish you was

503
00:26:22,441 --> 00:26:24,201
a bit more glass half-full,
sunshine.

504
00:26:24,321 --> 00:26:25,881
He's right, though.

505
00:26:26,001 --> 00:26:29,361
If anyone's got any heartfelt
end-of-life speeches,

506
00:26:29,481 --> 00:26:31,361
now is probably the moment.

507
00:26:31,481 --> 00:26:32,721
Er...

508
00:26:32,841 --> 00:26:34,721
Well...

509
00:26:34,841 --> 00:26:36,761
Oh, God, you're not actually
going to do that, are you?

510
00:26:38,321 --> 00:26:41,441
There must be
something we can do.

511
00:26:41,561 --> 00:26:42,601
(FLICKS SWITCHES)

512
00:26:42,721 --> 00:26:43,961
Why is all this shut down?

513
00:26:44,081 --> 00:26:45,041
We've got to conserve

514
00:26:45,161 --> 00:26:46,721
what little power
we've got left.

515
00:26:46,841 --> 00:26:48,641
(METALLIC THUD)

516
00:26:48,761 --> 00:26:50,321
What was that?

517
00:26:50,441 --> 00:26:51,521
(SCRAPING)

518
00:26:51,641 --> 00:26:52,641
I don't know.

519
00:26:52,761 --> 00:26:54,041
Any idea where we are?

520
00:26:54,161 --> 00:26:56,401
Middle of space.

521
00:26:56,521 --> 00:26:57,681
Dying slowly.

522
00:26:57,801 --> 00:27:00,321
Yes, thank you, Eeyore,
I got that much.

523
00:27:00,441 --> 00:27:01,681
Oi, you.

524
00:27:01,801 --> 00:27:05,121
How many times have we had
to get out of trouble together?

525
00:27:05,241 --> 00:27:06,441
There's only three of us now.

526
00:27:08,041 --> 00:27:09,921
We're just the scraps.

527
00:27:10,041 --> 00:27:13,281
Yeah, but we're still not gonna
go down without a fight.

528
00:27:13,401 --> 00:27:15,241
(THUD)

529
00:27:18,801 --> 00:27:20,921
YAZ: What are those noises?

530
00:27:21,041 --> 00:27:23,081
We were passing through
the old battlegrounds

531
00:27:23,201 --> 00:27:24,441
when everything failed.

532
00:27:26,321 --> 00:27:27,961
Who knows what's out there?

533
00:27:28,081 --> 00:27:30,521
I'm going to take a look.

534
00:27:30,641 --> 00:27:32,201
Oi, careful, will ya?

535
00:27:34,521 --> 00:27:37,401
(THUD)

536
00:27:39,721 --> 00:27:42,441
What's out there? Can you see
what's making the noises?

537
00:27:42,561 --> 00:27:44,201
Yeah.

538
00:27:46,161 --> 00:27:47,361
I can.

539
00:27:47,481 --> 00:27:49,881
(THUDS CONTINUE)

540
00:28:03,521 --> 00:28:05,281
And?

541
00:28:09,241 --> 00:28:10,441
Bits of dead Cybermen...

542
00:28:11,641 --> 00:28:13,121
...floating in space.

543
00:28:14,321 --> 00:28:16,241
Must be one of
the last battle sites.

544
00:28:16,361 --> 00:28:18,001
They're definitely dead,
though, right?

545
00:28:19,281 --> 00:28:20,521
Look, we're turning.

546
00:28:28,641 --> 00:28:30,161
What else can you see?

547
00:28:30,281 --> 00:28:32,161
Dormant ships.

548
00:28:33,401 --> 00:28:34,601
Loads of 'em.

549
00:28:35,961 --> 00:28:37,641
That's hope right there.

550
00:28:37,761 --> 00:28:39,161
Right, Graham?

551
00:28:39,281 --> 00:28:40,801
Yaz, jump down,
let's have a look.

552
00:28:42,761 --> 00:28:44,641
There you go, look.

553
00:28:44,761 --> 00:28:47,041
Now, that one at the front,
there's an opening in it,

554
00:28:47,161 --> 00:28:48,561
like a docking bay.

555
00:28:48,681 --> 00:28:50,201
If we could just get in there,
and get across there...

556
00:28:50,321 --> 00:28:52,081
We'd never reach it.
We don't have the power.

557
00:28:52,201 --> 00:28:53,521
Well, what about life support?

558
00:28:53,641 --> 00:28:55,481
Yeah.

559
00:28:55,601 --> 00:28:57,681
Channel the remaining energy
of those systems.

560
00:28:57,801 --> 00:28:59,801
That's what you need -
burst of acceleration.

561
00:29:00,961 --> 00:29:03,081
It might work.

562
00:29:04,281 --> 00:29:06,521
We could vent the air pressure.

563
00:29:06,641 --> 00:29:07,961
It could spin us enough.

564
00:29:08,081 --> 00:29:10,041
We'll lose all the oxygen,
we'll be dead.

565
00:29:10,161 --> 00:29:11,241
We're dead anyway!

566
00:29:12,321 --> 00:29:14,281
At least let's have a go, eh?

567
00:29:18,081 --> 00:29:19,361
- OK.
- YEDLARMI: So,

568
00:29:19,481 --> 00:29:21,921
we channel every last bit
of life support

569
00:29:22,041 --> 00:29:23,921
towards propulsion.
Everything off.

570
00:29:24,041 --> 00:29:25,041
Shut everything down.

571
00:29:25,161 --> 00:29:28,641
Any system that's still got
even the tiniest hint of power

572
00:29:28,761 --> 00:29:30,201
has got to go.

573
00:29:31,561 --> 00:29:34,601
- YEDLARMI: We must be mad.
- YAZ: Not mad.

574
00:29:34,721 --> 00:29:36,041
Hopeful.

575
00:29:41,481 --> 00:29:43,401
- OK.
- Don't panic.

576
00:29:43,521 --> 00:29:45,721
And don't take
any deep breaths,

577
00:29:45,841 --> 00:29:47,641
cos they ain't gonna come.

578
00:29:49,001 --> 00:29:50,441
We've been stranded
in space before.

579
00:29:50,561 --> 00:29:51,561
GRAHAM: Yeah.

580
00:29:55,441 --> 00:29:56,721
Here we go.

581
00:29:56,841 --> 00:29:57,841
Yeah.

582
00:30:06,801 --> 00:30:09,001
- (ALARM BLARES)
- Woo!

583
00:30:12,441 --> 00:30:14,681
(SCREAMING)

584
00:30:26,761 --> 00:30:29,961
(GROANS, EXHALES)

585
00:30:30,081 --> 00:30:31,561
We landed.

586
00:30:33,881 --> 00:30:35,241
I think we did! (LAUGHS)

587
00:30:37,681 --> 00:30:38,761
(CHUCKLES)

588
00:30:38,881 --> 00:30:39,881
(SIGHS)

589
00:30:42,801 --> 00:30:44,241
YEDLARMI:
Look at the size of this place.

590
00:30:44,361 --> 00:30:45,281
RAVIO: We must've come in

591
00:30:45,401 --> 00:30:46,641
through the docking bay
entrance.

592
00:30:46,761 --> 00:30:48,921
BESCOT: Well, good job
they left the doors open.

593
00:30:52,961 --> 00:30:55,921
We triggered automation sensors
as we came in,

594
00:30:56,041 --> 00:30:57,281
set everything going again.

595
00:30:59,041 --> 00:30:59,961
You two are lucky.

596
00:31:00,081 --> 00:31:01,801
We're not lucky, sunshine.

597
00:31:01,921 --> 00:31:03,961
We're persistent -
we never give up.

598
00:31:04,081 --> 00:31:05,361
Luckily for you.

599
00:31:07,401 --> 00:31:09,801
- Let's have a look around.
- Right.

600
00:31:20,361 --> 00:31:22,801
CYBERGUARD 1:
Exiting warp, leader.

601
00:31:22,921 --> 00:31:26,321
The trail of the human craft
ends here.

602
00:31:26,441 --> 00:31:31,441
CYBERGUARD 2: Human life signs
registering on carrier ship.

603
00:31:31,561 --> 00:31:33,601
Yes.

604
00:31:33,721 --> 00:31:36,401
The Cyberium sees all.

605
00:31:36,521 --> 00:31:40,001
Their destiny and ours,
intertwined.

606
00:31:40,121 --> 00:31:42,601
The site
of our greatest defeat...

607
00:31:42,721 --> 00:31:48,121
...and soon a shrine
for our rebirth.

608
00:31:49,241 --> 00:31:51,841
THE DOCTOR ON COMMS:
Shuttle calling Ko Sharmus.

609
00:31:51,961 --> 00:31:53,681
Anyone hear me?

610
00:31:53,801 --> 00:31:56,561
Anyone there on Ko Sharmus,
talk to me.

611
00:31:56,681 --> 00:31:57,721
Please?

612
00:31:57,841 --> 00:31:59,721
What I'd give for
a friendly voice right now.

613
00:31:59,841 --> 00:32:01,321
Go on, pleeease.

614
00:32:01,441 --> 00:32:04,281
Shuttle calling Ko Sharmus.

615
00:32:08,121 --> 00:32:09,721
(SHAKILY)
Ko Sharmus responding.

616
00:32:09,841 --> 00:32:12,241
Hello? Hello?

617
00:32:12,361 --> 00:32:13,641
We've made it!

618
00:32:13,761 --> 00:32:15,361
This is the Doctor, who's that?

619
00:32:15,481 --> 00:32:16,801
I've told you.

620
00:32:16,921 --> 00:32:18,761
This is Ko Sharmus.

621
00:32:18,881 --> 00:32:20,001
Ko Sharmus?

622
00:32:20,121 --> 00:32:21,721
You're a person, not a planet?

623
00:32:22,961 --> 00:32:25,441
Wh-who are you?
What do you want?

624
00:32:25,561 --> 00:32:26,801
We're human.

625
00:32:26,921 --> 00:32:28,401
We've come to cross
the Boundary.

626
00:32:28,521 --> 00:32:30,481
No, I don't think so.

627
00:32:30,601 --> 00:32:31,641
What do you mean?

628
00:32:31,761 --> 00:32:33,201
There are no more humans.

629
00:32:33,321 --> 00:32:34,601
Well, we've got news for you.

630
00:32:34,721 --> 00:32:36,361
First things first,
we're on a stolen Cybership,

631
00:32:36,481 --> 00:32:37,801
but we're not Cybermen,
we're friendly,

632
00:32:37,921 --> 00:32:38,841
and there's more on the way.

633
00:32:38,961 --> 00:32:40,881
Very much looking forward
to meeting you.

634
00:32:41,001 --> 00:32:42,281
Now forgive me,
I need to jump off.

635
00:32:42,401 --> 00:32:43,801
I have to land this thing
properly.

636
00:32:43,921 --> 00:32:45,121
(GRINDING)

637
00:32:46,521 --> 00:32:49,041
I'll just park this thing
over the ridge.

638
00:33:02,801 --> 00:33:04,281
RAVIO: (EXHALES)
It's so cold in here.

639
00:33:04,401 --> 00:33:05,521
Ah, see?

640
00:33:05,641 --> 00:33:07,841
That is cos you're alive
and breathing, cos of us.

641
00:33:07,961 --> 00:33:09,321
Are you going to keep
going on about that?

642
00:33:09,441 --> 00:33:11,241
Yes - every hour on the hour.

643
00:33:11,361 --> 00:33:13,241
(LAUGHS)

644
00:33:13,361 --> 00:33:14,641
What are you laughing at?

645
00:33:14,761 --> 00:33:16,281
You.

646
00:33:16,401 --> 00:33:17,841
What about me?

647
00:33:17,961 --> 00:33:20,521
You've come a long way,
Graham O'Brien.

648
00:33:20,641 --> 00:33:22,201
Thanks, Yaz.

649
00:33:22,321 --> 00:33:23,881
I raided
one of these carriers once -

650
00:33:24,001 --> 00:33:25,961
nearly got fried to death.

651
00:33:26,081 --> 00:33:27,521
Good times.

652
00:33:29,001 --> 00:33:31,201
Cyber Control should be
just down here.

653
00:33:31,321 --> 00:33:32,881
Wait.

654
00:33:33,001 --> 00:33:34,361
Is this a Cybership?

655
00:33:34,481 --> 00:33:35,641
War carrier.

656
00:33:35,761 --> 00:33:37,081
We get this working,

657
00:33:37,201 --> 00:33:40,201
it can get us to Ko Sharmus,
maybe even find your friends.

658
00:33:41,281 --> 00:33:42,561
GRAHAM: War carrier?

659
00:33:44,681 --> 00:33:46,321
Are you thinking
what I'm thinking?

660
00:33:46,441 --> 00:33:47,721
What was it carrying?

661
00:33:55,841 --> 00:33:58,481
YEDLARMI: This is
the control deck all right.

662
00:34:00,041 --> 00:34:02,121
- (POWERS UP)
- Systems still intact.

663
00:34:06,401 --> 00:34:07,801
Full power banks.

664
00:34:07,921 --> 00:34:09,641
This'll get us to Ko Sharmus.

665
00:34:09,761 --> 00:34:11,761
We could even use it
to cross the Boundary.

666
00:34:12,841 --> 00:34:14,521
Use it as a settlement ship

667
00:34:14,641 --> 00:34:16,041
till we find
the best habitable planet.

668
00:34:16,161 --> 00:34:17,401
- Yeah, that could work.
- Oh, careful,

669
00:34:17,521 --> 00:34:20,401
son, you sounded slightly
positive there for a sec.

670
00:34:20,521 --> 00:34:22,561
I'm going to take a look around
the rest of the carrier,

671
00:34:22,681 --> 00:34:24,681
see what else is here.

672
00:34:24,801 --> 00:34:26,201
I'll come with you -
it's safer with two.

673
00:34:26,321 --> 00:34:27,521
Go careful.

674
00:34:27,641 --> 00:34:28,841
GRAHAM: I was born careful!

675
00:34:29,921 --> 00:34:31,041
That's actually true.

676
00:34:31,161 --> 00:34:33,681
It's going to take a while
to reboot -

677
00:34:33,801 --> 00:34:35,961
have to go one section
at a time.

678
00:34:36,081 --> 00:34:37,841
(METALLIC CREAKING)

679
00:34:43,561 --> 00:34:45,481
Level 139.

680
00:34:45,601 --> 00:34:47,681
It's always been
my favourite level.

681
00:34:47,801 --> 00:34:49,441
It's as good as any.

682
00:34:50,961 --> 00:34:53,721
At least he's got the power
back on, though, eh?

683
00:34:53,841 --> 00:34:56,281
(WHOOSHING)

684
00:34:56,401 --> 00:34:58,041
- (THUD)
- Aah!

685
00:34:59,841 --> 00:35:01,321
They must have got us moving.

686
00:35:01,441 --> 00:35:02,441
Yeah.

687
00:35:03,761 --> 00:35:05,281
You know, I'm starting to think

688
00:35:05,401 --> 00:35:07,441
we're in with a good chance
of surviving today.

689
00:35:07,561 --> 00:35:09,041
Oh, not just today -
you've still got a lot of life

690
00:35:09,161 --> 00:35:10,121
ahead of you.

691
00:35:10,241 --> 00:35:11,601
Yeah, well,
I hope you're right.

692
00:35:13,921 --> 00:35:15,681
How do you reckon we get in?

693
00:35:15,801 --> 00:35:17,361
(DOORS CREAK)

694
00:35:18,481 --> 00:35:19,641
(AIR HISSES)

695
00:35:20,961 --> 00:35:23,201
Right. Let's have a butcher's.

696
00:35:27,201 --> 00:35:28,201
Butcher's hook?

697
00:35:28,321 --> 00:35:29,401
Look?

698
00:35:30,561 --> 00:35:32,561
It's cockney rhyming slang.

699
00:35:32,681 --> 00:35:34,841
No, don't worry about it.

700
00:35:34,961 --> 00:35:36,361
You are really strange.

701
00:35:36,481 --> 00:35:38,121
Excuse me,
I'm the most normal bloke

702
00:35:38,241 --> 00:35:39,441
you're ever going to meet.

703
00:35:39,561 --> 00:35:41,001
No, strange is a compliment!

704
00:35:43,361 --> 00:35:45,121
I like strange.

705
00:35:45,241 --> 00:35:46,281
Oh?

706
00:35:47,921 --> 00:35:49,441
Oh...

707
00:35:49,561 --> 00:35:50,721
Well...

708
00:35:55,761 --> 00:35:58,241
(MACHINERY POWERS UP)

709
00:36:09,361 --> 00:36:10,681
What do you reckon these are,
then?

710
00:36:10,801 --> 00:36:12,241
- (CLANK)
- (POWERS UP)

711
00:36:12,361 --> 00:36:13,681
Oop. Hello.

712
00:36:21,001 --> 00:36:23,361
- (DOOR CREAKS)
- (RHYTHMIC BEEPING)

713
00:36:38,801 --> 00:36:40,321
This was a troop carrier...

714
00:36:41,321 --> 00:36:43,001
...bringing soldiers
to the front.

715
00:36:44,321 --> 00:36:46,041
Fresh Cybermen ready to fight.

716
00:36:46,161 --> 00:36:48,681
(ELECTRICITY BUZZES)

717
00:36:48,801 --> 00:36:50,201
Warrior class.

718
00:36:55,041 --> 00:36:57,681
GRAHAM: There's got to be over
a thousand Cybermen in here.

719
00:36:57,801 --> 00:36:59,841
I counted ten doors
on each level.

720
00:36:59,961 --> 00:37:02,001
Well, how many levels
on this ship?

721
00:37:02,121 --> 00:37:03,761
Several hundred.

722
00:37:03,881 --> 00:37:05,801
And we're in the middle
of stealing it.

723
00:37:16,001 --> 00:37:18,401
We are home.

724
00:37:18,521 --> 00:37:21,721
The Cyberium
has called me to this task.

725
00:37:21,841 --> 00:37:24,721
And now its vision
shall be fulfilled.

726
00:37:24,841 --> 00:37:27,201
CYBERGUARDS: Hail the Cyberium.

727
00:37:31,481 --> 00:37:33,761
DOCTOR: Afternoon!
Or is it morning?

728
00:37:33,881 --> 00:37:35,721
Loving the coastline.

729
00:37:35,841 --> 00:37:38,041
KO SHARMUS: Three of you.

730
00:37:38,161 --> 00:37:41,241
Not just one, but three of you.

731
00:37:42,601 --> 00:37:44,481
(SHAKILY) I don't believe it.

732
00:37:44,601 --> 00:37:46,521
There's me
having lost all hope.

733
00:37:46,641 --> 00:37:48,321
Consider us your hope restored.

734
00:37:48,441 --> 00:37:50,921
I'm the Doctor.
This is Ryan and Ethan.

735
00:37:51,041 --> 00:37:52,481
Do you mind
if I have a shufty around?

736
00:37:52,601 --> 00:37:54,601
How are your defences here?

737
00:37:54,721 --> 00:37:56,281
Come on.

738
00:37:57,841 --> 00:37:59,521
Did this settlement
start with you?

739
00:37:59,641 --> 00:38:01,001
Yes.

740
00:38:01,121 --> 00:38:03,481
Myself and handful of others...

741
00:38:04,841 --> 00:38:07,241
...fleeing the Cybercamps.

742
00:38:08,801 --> 00:38:11,321
So you fought in the war?

743
00:38:11,441 --> 00:38:12,801
Yes.

744
00:38:12,921 --> 00:38:14,201
For a long time.

745
00:38:14,321 --> 00:38:17,761
Then I was captured and held
in 3 human internment camp

746
00:38:17,881 --> 00:38:21,081
for processing.
Sent for upgrade.

747
00:38:21,201 --> 00:38:24,161
I was one of the lucky ones
who got away.

748
00:38:25,241 --> 00:38:27,401
We had heard tell
of this place.

749
00:38:27,521 --> 00:38:30,521
We didn't really believe it,
but we managed to get here.

750
00:38:30,641 --> 00:38:32,361
The war hadn't made it
this far,

751
00:38:32,481 --> 00:38:35,961
so we built shelter
and over time, others came.

752
00:38:36,081 --> 00:38:37,361
The word spread.

753
00:38:37,481 --> 00:38:40,041
So...where's everyone else?

754
00:38:41,081 --> 00:38:42,601
There's only me.

755
00:38:44,281 --> 00:38:47,401
I helped everyone else
through the Boundary.

756
00:38:47,521 --> 00:38:50,641
And then, cos I'm an idiot...

757
00:38:52,081 --> 00:38:55,721
...I felt like it was
my duty to wait...

758
00:38:56,921 --> 00:38:58,841
...in case others came.

759
00:38:58,961 --> 00:39:00,121
(CHUCKLES SOFTLY)

760
00:39:02,001 --> 00:39:03,481
But it's been a long time.

761
00:39:04,601 --> 00:39:05,801
You sacrificed your own life

762
00:39:05,921 --> 00:39:08,041
on the chance others
were still out there?

763
00:39:08,161 --> 00:39:10,761
You make it sound more noble
than it is.

764
00:39:10,881 --> 00:39:12,681
So it's true?

765
00:39:12,801 --> 00:39:15,281
The Boundary, it's real?

766
00:39:15,401 --> 00:39:17,681
Of course it's real.

767
00:39:17,801 --> 00:39:19,561
Will you show us?

768
00:39:21,521 --> 00:39:24,761
(ALARM BLARES)

769
00:39:24,881 --> 00:39:26,841
I think this is trying
to tell us something.

770
00:39:30,961 --> 00:39:32,441
Oh, no.

771
00:39:32,561 --> 00:39:34,601
We've been boarded.

772
00:39:37,561 --> 00:39:40,321
- Open the comms channel.
- Yeah, yeah, I'm doing it.

773
00:39:44,761 --> 00:39:47,241
Graham, Ravio,
head to the control deck.

774
00:39:47,361 --> 00:39:48,801
Cybermen just boarded.

775
00:39:48,921 --> 00:39:51,921
(ON COMMS) Graham, Ravio,
this is Yaz.

776
00:39:52,041 --> 00:39:54,041
Cybermen have boarded
and are on your level.

777
00:39:54,161 --> 00:39:56,081
Get back here
as quick as you can.

778
00:39:56,201 --> 00:39:59,281
Yaz calling Graham and Ravio,
can you hear me?

779
00:39:59,401 --> 00:40:00,801
Yes, thank you!

780
00:40:12,801 --> 00:40:13,961
Wait.

781
00:40:32,681 --> 00:40:34,601
(WHIRRING)

782
00:40:39,721 --> 00:40:41,641
Abandoned no longer.

783
00:40:44,201 --> 00:40:47,881
Ascension is near!

784
00:40:49,921 --> 00:40:51,841
No wonder
they almost wiped us out.

785
00:40:51,961 --> 00:40:53,201
The systems on this ship

786
00:40:53,321 --> 00:40:55,441
are the most advanced
I've ever seen.

787
00:40:55,561 --> 00:40:57,721
Have you seen
the speed we're going at?

788
00:40:57,841 --> 00:41:00,201
It'd barely take us any time
to get to Ko Sharmus.

789
00:41:00,321 --> 00:41:01,721
Yeah, bringing
hundreds of thousands

790
00:41:01,841 --> 00:41:02,921
of dormant Cybermen with us.

791
00:41:03,041 --> 00:41:04,241
We can't do that.

792
00:41:05,281 --> 00:41:07,721
We cannot take Cybermen
to the Boundary.

793
00:41:07,841 --> 00:41:10,001
What are our other options?

794
00:41:11,281 --> 00:41:12,721
Surrender this ship?

795
00:41:12,841 --> 00:41:15,361
Land on another planet and
set the Cybermen loose there?

796
00:41:16,361 --> 00:41:18,281
We're gonna
keep all of you safe.

797
00:41:18,401 --> 00:41:19,841
We're gonna find the Doctor

798
00:41:19,961 --> 00:41:21,761
and we're gonna
take them Cybermen down.

799
00:41:22,841 --> 00:41:24,281
Aren't we, Graham?

800
00:41:26,161 --> 00:41:27,481
Yes, we are, Yaz.

801
00:41:27,601 --> 00:41:29,161
Totally. Very much so.

802
00:41:29,281 --> 00:41:31,361
That's some
high-level self-delusion.

803
00:41:32,401 --> 00:41:34,081
None of us are giving up, eh?

804
00:41:34,201 --> 00:41:35,241
Not now.

805
00:41:35,361 --> 00:41:36,681
Glass half-full, right?

806
00:41:39,361 --> 00:41:41,241
What do you think
they're doing down there?

807
00:41:41,361 --> 00:41:43,801
Let me activate the ob system.

808
00:41:43,921 --> 00:41:45,841
GRAHAM: They've opened up
those containers.

809
00:42:03,081 --> 00:42:05,841
Awaken, my soldiers.

810
00:42:09,041 --> 00:42:11,961
The ascension shall begin.

811
00:42:14,841 --> 00:42:17,921
(ROBOTIC SHRIEKING)

812
00:42:19,921 --> 00:42:22,601
(SHRIEKING INTENSIFIES)

813
00:42:27,921 --> 00:42:31,041
We're carrying a Cyberman

814
00:42:31,161 --> 00:42:34,561
that makes
other Cybermen scream.

815
00:42:34,881 --> 00:42:37,001
RYAN:
So where's this Boundary?

816
00:42:37,121 --> 00:42:38,761
Cos that's just the sea.

817
00:42:38,881 --> 00:42:41,081
This is where it starts,
every time.

818
00:42:42,161 --> 00:42:44,321
I've seen people go through.

819
00:42:45,401 --> 00:42:47,681
And I hope they're alive
and well elsewhere.

820
00:42:47,801 --> 00:42:50,081
That's quite a risk
everyone's taking.

821
00:42:50,201 --> 00:42:52,001
A leap into the unknown.

822
00:42:52,121 --> 00:42:55,521
It was preferable
to the alternative.

823
00:42:57,561 --> 00:43:00,361
If you want to see it,
step closer.

824
00:43:00,481 --> 00:43:02,281
It responds to proximity.

825
00:43:06,681 --> 00:43:07,801
A bit further...

826
00:43:07,921 --> 00:43:10,441
...and it will respond.

827
00:43:15,201 --> 00:43:16,321
(RUMBLING)

828
00:43:18,681 --> 00:43:20,321
Here it comes.

829
00:43:23,481 --> 00:43:25,481
How is that possible?

830
00:43:25,601 --> 00:43:29,001
I don't know, but it's good,
isn't it?

831
00:43:32,361 --> 00:43:35,201
KO SHARMUS: It's the last
way out of this galaxy.

832
00:43:37,761 --> 00:43:40,641
SERGEANT:
It's a sad day for us all here.

833
00:43:40,761 --> 00:43:41,721
But if any man can be said

834
00:43:41,841 --> 00:43:43,521
to have earned
a peaceful retirement,

835
00:43:43,641 --> 00:43:45,561
it's our Brendan.

836
00:43:45,681 --> 00:43:48,041
On behalf
of the local community

837
00:43:48,161 --> 00:43:50,561
and everyone past and present
who you've helped,

838
00:43:50,681 --> 00:43:52,601
we'd like to present you
with this memento.

839
00:43:53,881 --> 00:43:56,561
May we all live up
to the standards you've set us.

840
00:43:56,681 --> 00:43:58,761
#- Thank you, Brendan.
- Thank you, sir.

841
00:44:03,681 --> 00:44:06,081
(FOOTSTEPS)

842
00:44:11,321 --> 00:44:12,801
(TICKING)

843
00:44:22,041 --> 00:44:23,521
Hello, Brendan.

844
00:44:23,641 --> 00:44:26,361
Would you mind coming with us
to the back office?

845
00:44:45,081 --> 00:44:47,281
(CLOCK TICKS)

846
00:45:05,281 --> 00:45:08,281
We have to get rid of
everything, I'm afraid.

847
00:45:08,401 --> 00:45:09,481
Thank you for your service.

848
00:45:11,321 --> 00:45:13,881
We're sorry
you won't remember it.

849
00:45:17,041 --> 00:45:19,481
(SCREAMS)

850
00:45:27,721 --> 00:45:29,201
We're coming out of vortex.

851
00:45:29,321 --> 00:45:30,921
We're not far away.

852
00:45:32,001 --> 00:45:33,881
Close enough to send a signal,
warn 'em we're coming.

853
00:45:34,001 --> 00:45:35,321
I can help you do that.

854
00:45:36,641 --> 00:45:39,841
Guys, they're all waking up
down there.

855
00:46:22,881 --> 00:46:24,761
We know you're here.

856
00:46:26,161 --> 00:46:28,041
My warriors are coming for you.

857
00:46:46,041 --> 00:46:49,641
Yaz looking for The Doctor,
all frequencies.

858
00:46:49,761 --> 00:46:52,481
Yaz looking for The Doctor.

859
00:46:53,681 --> 00:46:56,081
Yaz, we can hear you.
Can you hear me?

860
00:46:58,921 --> 00:47:00,081
YAZ: Doctor!

861
00:47:00,201 --> 00:47:01,441
Where are you?

862
00:47:01,561 --> 00:47:03,801
We're on a Cyber battle
cruiser with that Cyber guy

863
00:47:03,921 --> 00:47:05,601
and a lot of Cyber troops
that are waking up.

864
00:47:09,681 --> 00:47:10,801
They're coming!

865
00:47:14,041 --> 00:47:16,361
They're right outside the door!

866
00:47:16,481 --> 00:47:18,681
Yaz, get off that ship - now.

867
00:47:18,801 --> 00:47:20,561
- We can't!
- (BANGING ON DOOR)

868
00:47:20,681 --> 00:47:22,681
We're trapped,
and they're about to break in.

869
00:47:22,801 --> 00:47:24,521
(BANGING CONTINUES)

870
00:47:27,081 --> 00:47:28,801
Yaz...

871
00:47:28,921 --> 00:47:30,641
Yaz!

872
00:47:30,761 --> 00:47:32,921
(RUMBLING)

873
00:47:37,841 --> 00:47:39,361
ETHAN: What is that?

874
00:47:40,521 --> 00:47:42,681
That's not possible.

875
00:47:42,801 --> 00:47:44,961
I've never seen it
look like that before.

876
00:47:45,081 --> 00:47:46,881
That's my home planet.

877
00:47:48,801 --> 00:47:50,761
That's Gallifrey.

878
00:48:00,801 --> 00:48:03,481
How is Gallifrey here?

879
00:48:05,761 --> 00:48:07,761
Wow! Ahh!

880
00:48:07,881 --> 00:48:11,201
Ah!
That's a good entrance, right?

881
00:48:13,481 --> 00:48:15,361
Be afraid, Doctor.

882
00:48:17,161 --> 00:48:20,401
Because everything
is about to change...

883
00:48:20,521 --> 00:48:21,801
...forever.

884
00:48:53,201 --> 00:48:56,081
THE MASTER: Look upon my work,
Doctor, and despair.

885
00:49:00,161 --> 00:49:01,481
We don't stand a chance here.

886
00:49:01,601 --> 00:49:04,001
We are stuck on a ship
stacked with Cybermen.

887
00:49:04,121 --> 00:49:05,241
THE MASTER: I told you before

888
00:49:05,361 --> 00:49:07,001
that everything you knew
was a lie.

889
00:49:07,121 --> 00:49:09,161
Well, now you get to
face the truth.

890
00:49:09,281 --> 00:49:10,881
KO SHARMUS:
You can be a pacifist tomorrow.

891
00:49:11,001 --> 00:49:14,241
Today, you have to survive.

892
00:49:14,361 --> 00:49:16,641
Set course for Gallifrey.

893
00:49:16,761 --> 00:49:18,041
Brace yourself.

894
00:49:20,521 --> 00:49:22,001
This is going to hurt.

